struct.name: AsyncActionProgress
struct.description: This records the progress of an asyncronous action.

structMember.name: actionName
structMember.description: The name of the invoked asynchronous action.

structMember.name: additionalInfo
structMember.description: Used for logging significant messages during execution of an action.

structMember.name: progressInfo
structMember.description: Textual information describing the actual state of the execution of the action.

structMember.name: progressPercentage
structMember.description: Progress of the action. The range is between 0 and 100.

structMember.name: result
structMember.description: Result state of completed action. This field has the value NOT_AVAILABLE if the action is not finished.

structMember.name: resultInfo
structMember.description: Textual description of the outcome/result of the action containing useful info for the NMS. It can contain an error message if the action failed.

structMember.name: actionId
structMember.description: Uniquely identifies the invocation of an action.

structMember.name: timeActionStarted
structMember.description: The date and time when the current action was started.

structMember.name: timeActionCompleted
structMember.description: The date and time when the action was completed (successfully or unsuccessfully).

structMember.name: timeOfLastStatusUpdate
structMember.description: The date and time when the struct member state was last updated.

structMember.name: value
structMember.description: The capacity value. The value is invalid if "noLimit=true".

structMember.name: noLimit
structMember.description: True if the value is unlimited, false if the value is defined by attribute "value".

enum.name: ActionResultType
enum.description: Lists the different results of an action.

enumMember.name: SUCCESS
enumMember.description: The asynchronous action has ended with success.

enumMember.name: FAILURE
enumMember.description: The asynchronous action has ended with failure.

enumMember.name: NOT_AVAILABLE
enumMember.description: No result is available yet.

enum.name: LmLicenseState
enum.description: The license state of a resource.

enumMember.name: DISABLED
enumMember.description: There is no valid license available for the feature or capacity.

enumMember.name: ENABLED
enumMember.description: There is valid license available for the feature or capacity.

enumMember.name: CANCELLING
enumMember.description: Cancellation is in progress.

enumMember.name: RUNNING
enumMember.description: The execution of the action is currently executing.

enumMember.name: FINISHED
enumMember.description: The action is finished.

enumMember.name: CANCELLED
enumMember.description: The action has been cancelled and the cancellation is done.

enum.name: LmState
enum.description: Operational modes of the License Manager.

enumMember.name: LOCKED
enumMember.description: No key file is available for the License Manager, so license requests are rejected.

enumMember.name: NORMAL
enumMember.description: Key file is available for the License Manager, so license requests are granted accordingly.

enumMember.name: INTEGRATION_UNLOCK
enumMember.description: All license requests are granted until first key file is delivered. The maximum duration the License Manager can function in this operational mode is pre-defined. When maximum duration expires and no other unlock applies, the License Manager goes into LOCKED operational state.

enumMember.name: MAINTENANCE_UNLOCK
enumMember.description: All license requests are granted for maintenance purposes. The maximum duration the License Manager can function in this operational state is pre-defined. When maximum duration expires and no other unlock applies, the License Manager goes into LOCKED operational state.

enumMember.name: EMERGENCY_UNLOCK
enumMember.description: All license requests are granted due to an emergency situation. The maximum duration the License Manager can function in this operational state is pre-defined. When maximum duration expires and no other unlock applies, the License Manager goes into LOCKED operational state.

enumMember.name: AUTONOMOUS_MODE
enumMember.description: The key file is not accessible and license requests are granted based on cached license information. The maximum duration the License Manager can function in this operational state is pre-defined. When maximum duration expires and no unlock state applies, the License Manager goes into LOCKED operational state.

enumMember.name: SYSTEM_TRIGGERED_UNLOCK
enumMember.description: SYSTEM_TRIGGERED_UNLOCK. All license requests are granted due to unlock state being triggered by some event in the License Manager. The maximum duration the License Manager can function in this operational state is pre-defined.

enum.name: LmServiceState
enum.description: Whether a certain service is operable or not based on license and feature states.

enum.name: LmArwaServerConnectionType
enum.description: Type of server connection for the Cloud system.

enumMember.name: PERMANENT
enumMember.description: PERMANENT. When LM is installed in Arwa permanent connection mode, application license keys are stored in the Arwa license repository.

enumMember.name: INTERMITTENT
enumMember.description: INTERMITTENT. In Arwa intermittent connection type the ME connects to Arwa at either scheduled pre-determined times (for example, monthly) or manually via an ECIM action. In intermittent connection type the connectivity to Arwa is assumed to be intermittent.

enum.name: LmActivationState
enum.description: Operational modes activation states and License Manager grace period.

enumMember.name: INACTIVE
enumMember.description: The operational mode or grace period is inactive.

enumMember.name: ACTIVATED
enumMember.description: The operational mode or grace period is activated.

enumMember.name: ACTIVATED_EXPIRING
enumMember.description: The operational mode or grace period is about to expire.

enumMember.name: EXPIRED
enumMember.description: The operational mode or grace period has expired. Note: The state is not applicable to all operational modes.

enumMember.name: UNDEFINED
enumMember.description: Enum value represents connection toward NeLS is established,

enumMember.name: CONNECTED
enumMember.description: Enum value represents connection toward NeLS is not established.

enumMember.name: NOT_CONNECTED
enumMember.description: Enum value represents initial state before connection attempt to NeLS.

enumMember.name: MANUAL
enumMember.description: MANUAL. The proxy's IP address and port are specified directly.

enum.name: LmFeatureState
enum.description: Indicates whether or not a certain feature is administratively activated.

derivedDataType.name: LmPercentageType
derivedDataType.description: Defines numeric data type with range 0..100 to express percentage.

derivedDataType.name: EcimPasswordString
derivedDataType.description: This type enables secure handling of passwords.

class.name: Lm
class.description: Supports activities and contains information related to license management.

action.name: refreshLicenseInventory
action.description: Initiates the synchronization of Managed Element's license inventory. Return value is true if the synchronization succeeded, otherwise false.

attribute.name: lmId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: fingerprint
attribute.description: The unique identification of the Managed Element.

attribute.name: fingerprintUpdateable
attribute.description: Indicates whether or not the fingerprint of the Managed Element can be updated.

attribute.name: lmState
attribute.description: The current operational state of the License Manager.

attribute.name: lastInventoryChange
attribute.description: Date and time of the last change in the license inventory. Change in the license inventory may occur when the key file is updated on the Managed Element or when license information is refreshed by synchronizing with license servers.

attribute.name: lastLicenseInventoryRefresh
attribute.description: Date and time when License Manager last synchronized the license inventory of the Managed Element.

attribute.name: referenceToLicenseServer
attribute.description: Reference to the primary license server used by the License Manager. For instance, the reference can contain the IP address of the server or locate its configuration interface. The attribute value is NULL if the License Manager does not rely on any license server.

class.name: FeatureKey
class.description: Key of a licensed feature that is available for the Managed Element.

attribute.name: featureKeyId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: state
attribute.description: State information for the feature associated with this key.

attribute.name: name
attribute.description: The name of the feature represented by the key.

attribute.name: validFrom
attribute.description: The date and time from which the key is valid.

attribute.name: expiration
attribute.description: The key expiry date and time. For perpetual keys, the value is NULL.

attribute.name: shared
attribute.description: Indicates whether the key is shared among Managed Elements or dedicated to the Managed Element. A key is dedicated to the Managed Element if the key can be used only by the Managed Element. This is always the case when the ELIM format is used. A key can be shared among multiple Managed Elements if it is installed on a License Server to which multiple Managed Elements connect.

attribute.name: keyId
attribute.description: Identity of the feature under license control. E.g., CXC4011234, FAT1021234

attribute.name: productType
attribute.description: Identifier of the type of product to which the capacity is related. This attribute is used only in systems where the different applications use separate key files to identify which application or product the capacity belongs to, e.g. “SASN”, “GSN_GGSN”, “SSR 8000”.

class.name: CapacityKey
class.description: Key of a licensed capacity that is available for the Managed Element.

attribute.name: capacityKeyId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: licensedCapacityLimit
attribute.description: Licensed capacity limit as defined in the installed key file.

attribute.name: capacityUnit
attribute.description: The licensed capacity measuring unit.

attribute.name: grantedCapacityLevel
attribute.description: The capacity level currently granted by the License Manager. The attribute value is based on requests and releases of capacity units made by License Users. If such requests and releases are not made by License Users, the value of the attribute defaults to the licensed capacity limit. Note: The value of the attribute is not based on Performance Management data.

attribute.name: licensedCapacityLimitReached
attribute.description: Indicates whether or not current capacity usage reaches the licensed capacity limit.

attribute.name: state
attribute.description: State information for the capacity associated with this key.

attribute.name: name
attribute.description: The name of the feature represented by the key.

attribute.name: validFrom
attribute.description: The date and time from which the key is valid.

attribute.name: expiration
attribute.description: The key expiry date and time. For perpetual keys, the value is NULL.

attribute.name: shared
attribute.description: Indicates whether the key is shared among Managed Elements or dedicated to the Managed Element. A key is dedicated to the Managed Element if the key can be used only by the Managed Element. This is always the case when the ELIM format is used. A key can be shared among multiple Managed Elements if it is installed on a License Server to which multiple Managed Elements connect.

attribute.name: keyId
attribute.description: Identity of the feature under license control. E.g., CXC4011234, FAT1021234

attribute.name: productType
attribute.description: Identifier of the type of product to which the capacity is related. This attribute is used only in systems where the different applications use separate key files to identify which application or product the capacity belongs to, e.g. “SASN”, “GSN_GGSN”, “SSR 8000”.

action.name: activate
action.description: Initiates activation of the Emergency Unlock operational mode. Return value is true if the activation succeeded, otherwise false.

attribute.name: emergencyUnlockId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: activationState
attribute.description: Activation state of Emergency Unlock.

attribute.name: expiration
attribute.description: Expiry date and time of Emergency Unlock. The value is NULL if the activation state is INACTIVE.

attribute.name: activationsLeft
attribute.description: Remaining allowed Emergency Unlock activations left.

action.name: activate
action.description: Initiates activation of the Integration Unlock operational mode. Return value is true if the activation succeeded, otherwise false.

attribute.name: integrationUnlockId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: activationState
attribute.description: Activation state of Integration Unlock.

attribute.name: expiration
attribute.description: Expiry date and time of Integration Unlock. The value is NULL if the activation state is INACTIVE.

attribute.name: activationsLeft
attribute.description: Remaining allowed Integration Unlock activations left.

action.name: activate
action.description: Initiates activation of the Maintenance Unlock operational mode. Return value is true if the activation succeeded, otherwise false.

attribute.name: maintenanceUnlockId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: activationState
attribute.description: Maintenance Unlock activation state.

attribute.name: expiration
attribute.description: Expiry date and time of Maintenance Unlock. The value is NULL if the activation state is INACTIVE.

attribute.name: activationsLeft
attribute.description: Remaining allowed Maintenance Unlock activations left.

attribute.name: systemTriggeredUnlockId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: activationState
attribute.description: System Triggered Unlock activation state.

attribute.name: expiration
attribute.description: Expiry date and time of System Triggered Unlock. The value is NULL if the activation state is INACTIVE.

attribute.name: autonomousModeId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: activationState
attribute.description: Autonomous Mode activation state.

attribute.name: expiration
attribute.description: Expiry date and time of Autonomous Mode. The value is NULL if the activation state is INACTIVE.

class.name: GracePeriod
class.description: Grace period information of the associated capacity.

attribute.name: gracePeriodId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: gracePeriodState
attribute.description: Grace period state of the capacity.

attribute.name: gracePeriodExpiration
attribute.description: Expiry date and time of the grace period. The value is NULL if grace-period state is inactive.

class.name: KeyFileManagement
class.description: Enables installation of key files and provides information about the installed key file.

action.name: installKeyFile
action.description: Initiates the key file installation defined by the URI given as a parameter. The return value is the action Id if the initiation succeeded, otherwise it is 0. The installation is an asynchronous operation. Progress is reported via attribute reportProgress.

parameter.name: uri
parameter.description: The URI of the key file that is to be installed. The URI may refer to a local (e.g., file://data/dir/subdir/rbs006.xml) or to a remote (e.g., sftp://myuser@myhostname.ericsson.local/dir/subdir/rbs006.xml) file. If user name is needed to access the referenced file then the URI shall include the user name. The URI must not contain password. The generic URI syntax is defined by RFC 2396.

parameter.name: password
parameter.description: Password to access the referenced file. If authentication is not password based, this parameter will be ignored.

attribute.name: keyFileManagementId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: reportProgress
attribute.description: Reference to the progress report including the result of the initiated key file installation.

class.name: KeyFileInformation
class.description: Basic information about the key file installed on the Managed Element.

attribute.name: keyFileInformationId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: sequenceNumber
attribute.description: Sequence number of the key file. If sequence number is not available, this value is 0.

attribute.name: installationTime
attribute.description: Date and time when key file was installed on the Managed Element.

attribute.name: locatable
attribute.description: Indicates whether or not the key file can currently be located.

attribute.name: productType
attribute.description: Identifier of the product type to which the capacity is related. This attribute is used only in systems where different applications use separate key files to identify to which application or product the capacity belongs, e.g: SASN, GSN_GGSN, or SSR 8000.

class.name: WarningThreshold
class.description: Warning threshold information of the associated capacity.

attribute.name: warningThresholdId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: warningThreshold
attribute.description: Defines the capacity usage level at which an alarm is raised. The threshold is expressed in terms of percentage in range 0-100, where 90 is default value.

attribute.name: warningThresholdReached
attribute.description: Indicates whether or not current capacity usage reaches warning threshold.

class.name: FeatureState
class.description: This MO class defines different licensing-related states of a feature.

attribute.name: featureStateId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: featureState
attribute.description: Indicates whether or not the feature license is administratively activated.

attribute.name: licenseState
attribute.description: Indicates whether or not a valid license key enables the feature usage.

attribute.name: serviceState
attribute.description: Indicates whether or not the feature is able to provide its service from a license perspective. The value of serviceState is derived from featureState and licenseState. If featureState is ACTIVATED and licenseState is ENABLED, serviceState is OPERABLE. In all other cases, serviceState is INOPERABLE.

attribute.name: description
attribute.description: The description of the feature.

attribute.name: featureKey
attribute.description: Key instances associated with this feature.

attribute.name: keyId
attribute.description: Identity of the feature under license control. E.g., CXC4011234, FAT1021234

class.name: CapacityState
class.description: States of capacities that are supported by a Managed Element.

attribute.name: capacityStateId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: licenseState
attribute.description: Indicates whether or not a valid license key enables the capacity usage.

attribute.name: description
attribute.description: The description of the capacity.

attribute.name: capacityKey
attribute.description: Key instances associated with this capacity.

attribute.name: keyId
attribute.description: Identity of the feature under license control. E.g., CXC4011234, FAT1021234

attribute.name: currentCapacityLimit
attribute.description: Licensed capacity limit as defined by the currently valid license key.

attribute.name: capacityUnit
attribute.description: The licensed capacity measuring unit.

attribute.name: grantedCapacityLevel
attribute.description: The capacity level currently granted by the License Manager. The attribute value is based on requests and releases of capacity units made by License Users. If such requests and releases are not made by License Users, the value of the attribute defaults to the licensed capacity limit. Note: The value of the attribute is not based on Performance Management data.

attribute.name: licensedCapacityLimitReached
attribute.description: Indicates whether or not current capacity usage reaches the licensed capacity limit.

attribute.name: featureState
attribute.description: Feature State for the new optional capacity licenses.

attribute.name: serviceState
attribute.description: Service State for the new optional capacity licenses.

attribute.name: range
attribute.description: Min and max value Min used when no licese and Max when EmergencyUnlock.

attribute.name: capacityLimitType
attribute.description: N/A

attribute.name: allocationLimit
attribute.description: Limit for allocation of capacity from NeLS.

attribute.name: neLSConfigurationId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: host
attribute.description: IPv6, IPv4 or DNS name.

attribute.name: port
attribute.description: The port number that is used to connect to NeLS.

attribute.name: connectionStatus
attribute.description: Represents status of the connection toward NeLS.

class.name: ArwaConfiguration
class.description: Enables configuration of the Arwa server connection properties.

action.name: installCustomerMetadataFile
action.description: Initiates the installation of the Client Metadata file defined by the URI given as parameter. e.g. installClientMetadataFile file:///tmp/clientMetadata.xml Return value is TRUE in case the initiation succeeded or FALSE otherwise.

parameter.name: uri
parameter.description: The URI of the metadatafile file that is to be installed. The URI may refer to a local (e.g., file:///data/dir/subdir/rbs006.xml) or to a remote (e.g., sftp://myuser@myhostname.ericsson.local/dir/subdir/rbs006.xml) file. If user name is needed to access the referenced file then the URI shall include the user name. The URI must not contain password. The generic URI syntax is defined by RFC 2396.

parameter.name: password
parameter.description: Password to access the referenced file. If authentication is not password based, this parameter will be ignored.

action.name: createUsageReport
action.description: createUsageReport. To be used as: createUsageReport URI startDate endDate [filter-reg-ex] i.e. createUsageReport /tmp/myUsageReport 2015-03-01 2015-03-15

parameter.name: uri
parameter.description: URI for destination of the usage report.

parameter.name: startDate
parameter.description: StartDate for the period of the usage report.

parameter.name: endDate
parameter.description: End date for the period of the usage report.

parameter.name: filter
parameter.description: Usage. filter-reg-ex An optional filter to customize the usage report. e.g. license=FAT123

action.name: connectToArwa
action.description: connectToArwa will provide the action id result if the invocation is successful.

attribute.name: arwaConfigurationId
attribute.description: Holds the name used when identifying the MO.

attribute.name: referenceToProxyServer
attribute.description: Identifies the uri address to be used for the proxy server. i.e. "https://proxy.foo.com:8080"

attribute.name: proxyServerUser
attribute.description: Username for the optional proxy server used to connect to Arwa.

attribute.name: proxyServerPw
attribute.description: Password for the optional proxy server used to connect to Arwa.

attribute.name: proxyServerType
attribute.description: Proxy server type to be used, can be MANUAL or AUTOMATIC.

attribute.name: licenseServerLastSuccessfulConnectTime
attribute.description: Last time of successful connection. i.e. “Fri, Dec 19, 2014 12:41:39 PM”

attribute.name: customerName
attribute.description: Name of the current customer. (e.g. Customer1)

attribute.name: maxAggregationFileSize
attribute.description: To define the maximum size of aggregation files in Kilobytes. If set to NULL there will be no files created (Turned off).

attribute.name: maxNumberOfIntermediaryAggregationFiles
attribute.description: Maximum number of the intermediary aggregation files to be used by the report tool.

attribute.name: arwaLicenseServerConnectionType
attribute.description: Type of connectivity for the Proxy server, can be PERMANENT or INTERMITTENT.

attribute.name: reportProgress
attribute.description: Reports if the Arwa connection was successful or not.

attribute.name: licenseServerPlannedConnectEvent
attribute.description: Next Schedule for a planned connection to the Arwa server. NULL if it is PERMANENT connection
